Advantages and Limitations of Naïve Bayes

Discussed the strengths and weaknesses of the algorithm.

Advantages:

Simple and easy to implement.
Fast training and prediction.
Performs well with large datasets.
Handles high-dimensional data efficiently.
Requires less training data.

Limitations:

Assumes feature independence.
Performance decreases when features are highly correlated.
May not perform well on complex datasets with dependent variables.
